Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @baguette{2} widthways at an angle into 2 cm slices.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Lay the slices onto a lined #baking tray{}. Bake in the oven until golden brown, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

Once the crostini have toasted, add the @grated cheese{50%grams}, @cream cheese{32%grams},
@creme fraiche{110%grams} and half the @mustard{1/2%sachet} to a #bowl{} and mix to combine.

Spread the cheese mixture over the top of the crostini.

Return to the top shelf until the cheese is melted and golden, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{5%grams} (use #scissors{} if you prefer).

Once cooked, remove the crostini from the oven. Allow to cool a little before serving.

Transfer to your #serving platter{} and sprinkle over the chopped chives to finish.